title: Bug 121170 - The IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method should return user recognizable strings
description: When calling the IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method before and after data extraction, the results are different.
OB: Currently, when calling the IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method before data extraction, it does not return user recognizable strings.
EB: The IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method should return user recognizable strings before and after data extraction.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Call the IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method before data extraction.
2. Note the result.
3. Call the IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method after data extraction.
4. Note the result.
Expected result: The IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method should return the same user recognizable strings before and after data extraction.
